crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis:
The script operates as a client for a remote Mimikatz RPC server. It parses command-line arguments to specify a target, authentication credentials (username, password, domain, NTLM hashes, or Kerberos with an optional AES key), and an optional file containing commands.

The script establishes a DCE/RPC connection to the target and binds to the Mimikatz RPC interface. It then performs a Diffie-Hellman key exchange to derive a shared ARC4 session key. Subsequent commands sent to the remote Mimikatz server are encoded, null-terminated, encrypted with this ARC4 session key, and transmitted via the `hMimiCommand` RPC call. Responses from the server are received encrypted and then decrypted using the same ARC4 session key before being displayed.

The script offers an interactive shell environment for issuing commands to the remote Mimikatz server or can execute a sequence of commands read from a specified file. Additionally, it includes functionality to execute arbitrary system commands locally on the machine running the script via `os.popen`.
